{"word":"H3372 - יָרֵא - yârêʼ - yaw-ray' - Affright","slug":"H3372","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">יָרֵא</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>yârêʼ"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>yaw-ray'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Affright"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D9;&#x05E8;&#x05D0; - ya&#x0302;re&#x0302;'</b> - <i>yaw-ray'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>fear</i>; morally to <i>revere</i>; causatively to <i>frighten: - </i>affright, be (make) afraid, dread (-ful), (put in) fear (-ful, -fully, -ing). (be had in) reverence (-end), X see, terrible (act, -ness, thing)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3373\">H3373</a>, <a href=\"#/H3374\">H3374</a>, <a href=\"#/H3375\">H3375</a>, <a href=\"#/H4172\">H4172</a>, <a href=\"#/H8493\">H8493</a>"}]}